article.headline: Air Force 63, Northern Colorado 54
article.story: AIR FORCE ACADEMY, Colo. (AP) -- Matt McCraw scored 17 points and Air Force overcame a slow start to defeat the University of Northern Colorado 63-54 on Thursday night. Air Force (5-2) fell behind 7-0 after missing eight straight shots and hit just 37 percent from the field in the first half. Nick Welch hit a 3-pointer to give the Falcons their first lead at 13-12 and Air Force led 29-24 at halftime. Welch finished with 15 and Antoine Hood had 10. Sean Nolen and Erik Olson each had 12 points for Northern Colorado (1-7), which is playing its second season at Division I. Nolen's 10-foot jumper late in the first half briefly tied the game at 24. Air Force improved to 55 percent from the field in the second half and built a 56-46 lead with 3:37 left. Northern Colorado cut the lead to six before the Falcons sealed the victory in the final minute. UNC shot 51 percent for the game and hit 92 percent of its free-throws. Air Force hit 62 percent from the line.
